docs.abstract: The strike by the United Auto Workers, in its fifth day, is causing layoffs in related operations but has not yet resulted in shortages at dealers.
docs.snippet: The strike by the United Auto Workers, in its fifth day, is causing layoffs in related operations but has not yet resulted in shortages at dealers.
docs.lead_paragraph: The strike that has shut down General Motors plants in the United States since Monday is starting to ripple through the automaker’s supply chain, causing layoffs and production stoppages by parts makers and components manufacturers across the Midwest.

headline.main: G.M. Walkout Begins to Pinch Suppliers and Canada Plants

docs.abstract: Robert A. Iger, Disney’s chief executive and chairman, had been on the board since 2011. But both companies will debut streaming services next month.
docs.snippet: Robert A. Iger, Disney’s chief executive and chairman, had been on the board since 2011. But both companies will debut streaming services next month.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Robert A. Iger, Disney’s chief executive and chairman, has resigned from the board of Apple, whose growing Hollywood operation would have made it harder for him to fully engage as one of its directors.

headline.main: Iger Departs Board of Apple, Disney’s New Streaming Competitor
headline.print_headline: Disney’s Chief Departs From Board of Apple

docs.abstract: Prince Abdulaziz bin Salman was named energy minister less than a week before an aerial attack crippled Saudi Arabia’s oil production.
docs.snippet: Prince Abdulaziz bin Salman was named energy minister less than a week before an aerial attack crippled Saudi Arabia’s oil production.
docs.lead_paragraph: A little over a week ago, Prince Abdulaziz bin Salman finally attained the job for which he had long prepared: energy minister of Saudi Arabia, one of the most crucial positions in the country.

headline.main: ​Job One for Saudis’ New Energy Chief: Picking Up the Pieces
headline.print_headline: After Airstrikes, New Saudi Energy Chief Seeks to Rebuild and Reassure

docs.abstract: Protests from Australia to San Francisco denounced the employment practices of ride-hailing companies. “I believe we deserve some respect and to be paid fairly,” one driver said.
docs.snippet: Protests from Australia to San Francisco denounced the employment practices of ride-hailing companies. “I believe we deserve some respect and to be paid fairly,” one driver said.
docs.lead_paragraph: A day of strikes planned by Uber drivers in cities around the world drew a modest turnout on Wednesday, as protesters denounced the ride-hailing giant’s employment and pay practices before its blockbuster initial public offering this week.

headline.main: Uber Drivers’ Day of Strikes Circles the Globe Before the Company’s I.P.O.
headline.print_headline: Strike by Uber Drivers Goes Global Ahead of I.P.O.

byline.original: By Kate Conger, Vicky Xiuzhong Xu and Zach Wichter

docs.abstract: Restaurant owners say Grubhub’s business model has cut into their profit margins. A New York City Council committee is investigating.
docs.snippet: Restaurant owners say Grubhub’s business model has cut into their profit margins. A New York City Council committee is investigating.
docs.lead_paragraph: Seamless, the food delivery service started two decades ago in Midtown Manhattan, calls itself “the most New York app in New York.” In advertisements, the company cracks jokes about the L train and takes unsubtle jabs at New Jersey. “Eat Like a True New Yorker,” one subway ad declares.

headline.print_headline: No Longer Savoring The Grubhub Effect

docs.abstract: While the largest gatherings still go to the biggest cities, more smaller cities are playing up their distinct offerings. Hence, the Floating Pavilion in Rotterdam.
docs.snippet: While the largest gatherings still go to the biggest cities, more smaller cities are playing up their distinct offerings. Hence, the Floating Pavilion in Rotterdam.
docs.lead_paragraph: Cannes has been a hub for meetings and events since the Cannes Film Festival began in 1946. But, said Régis Faure, director of tourism for Cannes, the gatherings are moving beyond the convention center, the Palais des Festivals et des Congrès, and are looking “more and more like a festival.”

headline.main: As Business Conferences Change, Their Hosts Are Changing, Too

docs.abstract: Growth in global trade is slowing dramatically as the world economy weakens and as the United States and China escalate their trade war.
docs.snippet: Growth in global trade is slowing dramatically as the world economy weakens and as the United States and China escalate their trade war.
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — As President Trump intensifies his trade war with China, and as factories slow in major industrial nations, world commerce is deteriorating rapidly, a perilous development that threatens the health of the global economy.

headline.main: Global Trade Is Deteriorating Fast, Sapping the World’s Economy
headline.print_headline: Trade Clashes Are Weakening Global Growth

docs.abstract: General Motors made cost concessions to get the union to accept the shutdown of three plants — a priority that Ford and Fiat Chrysler don’t have.
docs.snippet: General Motors made cost concessions to get the union to accept the shutdown of three plants — a priority that Ford and Fiat Chrysler don’t have.
docs.lead_paragraph: The tentative contract that General Motors has worked out with the United Automobile Workers union is going to raise the automaker’s cost of labor and require a significant cash outlay.

headline.main: G.M. Contract Terms May Be a Tougher Fit for Its Rivals
headline.print_headline: Contract Terms May Not Work For G.M. Rivals

docs.abstract: The chief executive is expected to testify on Wednesday at a House committee hearing about his company’s cryptocurrency project.
docs.snippet: The chief executive is expected to testify on Wednesday at a House committee hearing about his company’s cryptocurrency project.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Mark Zuckerberg hopes that one day, in the not too distant future, billions of people will use a cryptocurrency created by Facebook to send money to friends and family around the world.

headline.main: Zuckerberg to Admit That Facebook Has Trust Issues
headline.print_headline: Zuckerberg Set to Admit Facebook’s Trust Issues
